.TH "locks_mandatory_area" 9 "locks_mandatory_area" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
locks_mandatory_area \- Check for a conflicting lock
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" locks_mandatory_area
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "loff_t start "  ","
.BI "loff_t end "  ","
.BI "unsigned char type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
the file to check
.IP "filp" 12
how the file was opened (if it was)
.IP "start" 12
first byte in the file to check
.IP "end" 12
lastbyte in the file to check
.IP "type" 12
F_WRLCK for a write lock, else F_RDLCK
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Searches the inode's list of locks to find any POSIX locks which conflict.
